text: A post about people who comment  America is a continent not a country  every time someone calls the US America on the internet Personally  I believe this misconception arises because of certain linguistic and cultural differences between English and other languages  For one   America  is not a continent   the Americas  make up   continents and  America  is reserved for the idea of the  New World  at times or  usually  a shortening of the name for the US  However  the synonym of America in other languages  Am rica in Spanish  Amerique in French   are the word for what in English is The Americas  two continents  and is seen elsewhere as   So  this cultural and linguistic difference causes mistranslation when these words are viewed as synonyms  because their meanings differ  So  you get people who falsely equate them and lack the understanding of the language difference and so see America as referring to what a native calls The Americas
summary: There is a misconception that America is a continent and not a country. The difference between English and other languages makes people mistranslate the two words and mistake them for each other.       in Spanish Amerique in French is the word for The Americas.
